With companies demanding a greater level of sophistication from their Electronic Point of Sale (EPoS) system it can be hard to choose the right combination of hard and software for your company. This can be especially difficult for Trade and Wholesale businesses as most products on the market are directed at retail and hospitality industries. Wholesalers and B2B companies have a completely different set of needs to those of shops, cafes and tourist attractions and in the past the features that they require to keep a closer control of their stock and accounts have not been well documented.  A good example of a key Wholesale EPoS feature would be unlimited quantity purchase features. Unlike B2C companies, the numbers of products that are bought at any one time tend to be much higher with Wholesalers. Products are bought in bulk and quantity levels can run into hundreds if not thousands of products. Therefore an ideal solution would be an EPoS system that has the Back Office Accounting functionality to handle these levels of stock. Traditionally this has been a key problem with many accounts packages unable to handle these figures.
